<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,346,612]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,298,386,412]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</emphasis>
Kraepelin (1913) recorded 
<taxonomicName authority="Pocock, 1890" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1890" box="[625,986,386,412]" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[625,819,386,411]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Chaerilus pictus</emphasis>
Pocock, 1890
</taxonomicName>
for the first time from 
<collectingRegion box="[1259,1346,386,412]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Xizang</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1358,1432,386,412]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">China</collectingCountry>
. He cited 
<specimenCount box="[258,366,426,452]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
from Daphla Hills in 
<collectingRegion box="[629,690,426,452]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Tibet</collectingRegion>
(today XizangChina) which we did not examine. Recently, Qi, Zhu &amp; Loureno (2005) re-recorded 
<taxonomicName authority="Pocock" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1890" box="[571,769,466,492]" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[571,676,466,491]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">C. pictus</emphasis>
Pocock
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of 
<specimenCount box="[955,1057,466,492]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="female">8 female</specimenCount>
specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[1259,1346,466,492]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Xizang</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1358,1432,466,492]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">China</collectingCountry>
. After consulting the works of 
<bibRefCitation author="Tikader, B. K. &amp; Bastawade, D. B." box="[514,860,506,532]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" refId="ref6436" refString="Tikader, B. K. &amp; Bastawade, D. B. (1983) The Fauna of India. Vol. 3. Scorpions (Scorpionida: Arachnida). Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta, 671 pp." type="book" year="1983">Tikader &amp; Bastawade (1983)</bibRefCitation>
and Kovak (2000), the present authors have reconsidered the identification made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Qi, J. X. &amp; M. S. Zhu &amp; R. W. Lourenco" box="[599,778,546,572]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref6306" refString="Qi, J. X., M. S. Zhu &amp; R. W. Lourenco (2005) Eight new species of the genera Scorpiops Peters, Euscorpiops Vachon, and Chaerilus Simon (Scorpiones: Eucorpiidae, Chaerilidae) from Tibet and Yunnan, China. Euscorpius, 32, 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="2005">Qi et al.(2005)</bibRefCitation>
and now believe that their description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1890" box="[1267,1371,546,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[1267,1371,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">C. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a misidentification.
</paragraph>
